 Nollywood stars Iyabo Ojo and Fathia Balogun have finally settled their long time beef and throwing shade on social media. Taking to Instagram, the two made the news known as they share photos of themselves excitedly posing for the camera, Captioning the post, Iyabo Ojo noted that it’s all about peace and love with Faithia Balogun and jokingly questioned how they will start following each other on Instagram since they blocked themselves. Iyabo Ojo also tagged Chairman of National Union of Road Transport worker, MC Oluomo and veteran actor Olaiye Igwe to her post, insinuating they have played a role in settling the long time beef. Iyabo Ojo wrote: It’s all peace & love faithiawilliams. How we go take follow each other again remain o chai …… ig expert over to you. Thank you @kingmcoluomo @olaiyaigwefilms. READ ALSO: Iyabo Ojo Reacts To Fathia Balogun’s Engagement (Photo) Similarly, Faithia Balogun also took to her Instagram page to share her and Iyabo Ojo photos, confirming they have settled their rift. She also appreciated MC Oluomo and Olaiye Igwe and prayed for more wisdom and understanding. She wrote: Happy new year iy..@iyaboojodespris ..@kingmcoluomo @olaiyaigwefilms .more wisdom and understanding..let peace reign. See post below:   A post shared by Oba Alice Iyabo Ojo (@iyaboojofespris) 